    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2017-12-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2017-12-29T15:33:17Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow distributions from qualified tuition programs (known as 529 plans) to be used for certain expenses associated with registered apprenticeship programs. </p> <p>The bill expands the definition of &quot;qualified higher education expenses&quot; for which tax-free distributions are allowed to include books, supplies, and equipment required for the enrollment or attendance of a designated beneficiary in an apprenticeship program registered and certified with the Department of Labor. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>A bill to amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to allow for distributions from 529 accounts for expenses associated with registered apprenticeship programs.</title>
